{"ts":"2026-07-19T03:43:08.808Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"GH-603. After a lossy merge resolution (.toon taken from one side, history union-merged), pm history-repair re-anchors by appending a reverting patch that discards the other author's mutation from effective state; validate then reports drift 0 / ok:true. A teammate agent's change is reverted invisibly — data loss is cemented. Fix direction: repair must emit an explicit revert warning naming discarded events/authors, expose a post-repair divergence signal in validate/health, and document a re-application recovery path. Detection half = pm-ol3p strict verify gate."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T03:43:08.808Z"}],"before_hash":"6260e12ef0612238b8ea3b715982a841faa011c6fe1a350d0994eecaa3f0475e","after_hash":"28daff28a71ea35e6f0d3e26a4ea068b1b62d41eae11cf389e018e49e49de901"}
